, rights-based politics, academic freedom, decolonization, and neoliberal capitalism.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aAcademic freedomzPalestine. 0aAcademic freedomzUnited States. 0aArab-Israeli conflictxSocial aspects. 0aBoycottszPalestiney21st century. 0aBoycottszUnited Statesy21st century. 70(DE-601)1048262900(DE-588)4041158-8aNahostkonflikt2gnd 70(DE-601)1054610670(DE-588)4162597-3aIsraelisch-Arabische Kriege2gnd 70(DE-601)1056860690(DE-588)4132654-4aBoykott2gnd 70(DE-601)1063994620(DE-588)4000888-5aAkademische Freiheit2gnd 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Israel & Palestine.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520967854423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520967854.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles